<vulnerability_guide>
  <title>ADVERSARIAL ML ATTACKS</title>

  <critical>Adversarial attacks craft inputs that fool machine learning models while appearing normal to humans. These attacks can bypass security-critical ML systems like malware detection, facial recognition, fraud detection, and content moderation. Small, carefully calculated perturbations cause dramatic misclassifications.</critical>

  <scope>
    - Adversarial example generation
    - Evasion attacks
    - Black-box attacks
    - Physical adversarial examples
    - Model robustness testing
    - Defense bypass techniques
  </scope>

