  </validation>

  <pro_tips>
    - Adversarial examples often transfer between models
    - Physical attacks must be robust to viewing conditions
    - Black-box attacks are slower but more realistic
    - Preprocessing defenses can often be bypassed
    - FGSM is fast but weak; PGD/C&W are stronger
    - Test at multiple epsilon values (perturbation budgets)
  </pro_tips>

  <remember>Machine learning models are fundamentally fragile to adversarial inputs. If a security decision depends on ML classification, adversarial attacks are a relevant threat. White-box attacks need model access but are powerful; black-box attacks are realistic but slower. Always test ML security systems with adversarial examples before trusting them in production.</remember>
</vulnerability_guide>
